free_txt: A sphere counter consisting of eight BF3 counters
embedded radially in a polyethylene sphere of 60-cm
diameter.
Several silicon surface-barrier detectors was
used to measure the yield of scattered alpha particles.
The error in the current integration is
less than 1%
The statistical error in the neutron yield
measurement was generally less than 2% (for cross
sections less than a few millibarns the  statistical
uncertainties are larger)
The efficiency of the neutron detector is
known to 3%
The uncertainty in the determination of
the background neutrons is normally 3 to 4%.
The standard error of all of the target
thicknesses was estimated to be 6%.
5.The standard error in the cross section for each
reaction was taken to be the square root of the sum
of the squares of the errors mentioned above and is
generally about 8%.
